    "id": "esdee-paints-fast-drying-synthetic-enamel",
    "slug": "esdee-paints-fast-drying-synthetic-enamel",
    "uri": "/products/esdee-paints-fast-drying-synthetic-enamel",
    "name": "Esdee Paints Fast Drying Synthetic Enamel",
    "brand": "Esdee Paints",
    "category": "Idustrial Paints",
    "shortDescription": "A high-performance architectural and industrial enamel engineered to deliver a rich, high-gloss finish with accelerated drying times for wood and metal surfaces.",
    "content": "A high-performance architectural and industrial enamel engineered to deliver a rich, high-gloss finish with accelerated drying times for wood and metal surfaces.\n\nEsdee Paints Fast Drying Synthetic Enamel is a premium alkyd-based coating designed for rapid turnaround projects where time and durability are critical. Formulated with high-grade resins, it forms a tough, weather-resistant structural barrier that dries significantly faster than standard decorative enamels. Perfect for both interior and exterior applications, it provides excellent color and gloss retention over structural steel, gates, grilles, windows, commercial vehicles, and industrial machinery, protecting them effectively from rust, weathering, and abrasions.\n\n---\n\n## Key Features & Benefits\n\n* **Accelerated Fast-Drying Formulation**\n  Significantly cuts down standard enamel drying intervals, allowing for quicker handling of components, minimized dust pick-up, and rapid multi-coat applications.\n  \n* **Brilliant Mirror High Gloss Sheen**\n  Provides a stunning, highly reflective gloss or smooth semi-gloss level that instantly updates the appearance of architectural fixtures and industrial machinery.\n\n* **Heavy-Duty Weather & Corrosion Defense**\n  Builds a dense, non-porous protective film that shields wood and ferrous metal substrates from intense humidity, rain, saline conditions, and daily mechanical wear.\n\n* **Outstanding Adhesion & Surface Elasticity**\n  Possesses superior anchoring properties that deeply bond to primed surfaces, expanding and contracting dynamically without cracking, blistering, or peeling.\n\n* **Excellent Washability & Scrub Resistance**\n  The hardened synthetic film makes it incredibly easy to wash down or wipe away grease, engine oils, and household stains with mild cleaning solutions.\n\n---\n\n## Technical Specifications\n\n| Specification | Details |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **Finish / Sheen Options** | High Gloss |\n| **Base Chemistry Type** | Oil-Based / Solvent-Based (Premium Alkyd Resins) |\n| **Recommended Substrates** | Mild Steel, Wrought Iron, Structural Frameworks, Commercial Vehicles, and Seasoned Wood |\n| **Surface Dry Time** | 1 to 2 Hours (Accelerated speed compared to standard 4-6 hour enamels) |\n| **Hard Dry / Recoating Interval** | 6 to 8 Hours (Dries completely uniform overnight) |\n| **Thinner Required** | Esdee Synthetic Enamel Thinner / Mineral Turpentine Oil (MTO) |\n| **Available Packaging** | 50ml, 100ml, 200ml, 500ml, 1L, 4L, and 20L |\n\n---\n\n## Estimated Coverage\n\n> **Note:** Actual spreading and coverage profiles can fluctuate based on the specific surface profile, substrate porosity, roughness, and paint application technique.\n\n* **On Smooth, Correctly Primed Metal/Wood (Brushing/Spraying):**\n  * **1 Coat:** 140 – 160 sq.ft / Litre\n  * **2 Coats:** 70 – 85 sq.ft / Litre\n\n---\n\n## Application Steps\n\n### 1. Hard Core Surface Preparation\n* Ensure the target substrate is completely structural, clean, dry, and free of moisture, chemical oils, mill-scale grease, and heavy dirt.\n* **For Metal Surfaces:** Scrape away existing structural rust, flaking old paint layers, and corrosion deposits aggressively using a hard wire brush or mechanical grinder. Sand smooth with **Emery Paper 180** and wipe clean.\n* **For Wooden Surfaces:** Sand directly along the direction of the natural wood grains using **Emery Paper 180** to pull off splinters and resin wood sap.\n\n### 2. Primary Anti-Corrosive Priming\n* **Metal Applications:** Apply 1 or 2 coats of *Esdee Syncoat Zinc Phosphate Primer* or *Red Oxide Metal Primer* to lock out oxidation paths. Allow the primer to dry fully before proceeding.\n* **Wood Applications:** Coat the bare substrate with 1 uniform layer of a reliable oil-based wood primer. Let it cure, then sand it very lightly with fine emery paper.\n\n### 3. Surface Leveling (Putty)\n* Apply a professional-grade knifing paste or metal filler over surface joints, structural holes, dents, or deep scratch abrasions. \n* Allow the filler to dry completely hard, sand it back flat using **Emery Paper 180** or **240**, and remove all loose powder residue.\n\n### 4. Topcoat Enamel Painting\n* Stir the container thoroughly before opening. Dilute the Fast Drying Synthetic Enamel with Esdee Thinner or MTO. Add roughly 8%–10% thinner for brush or roller setups, or 15%–20% for automated spray equipment.\n* Apply the **1st Topcoat** in uniform, sweeping strokes. Thanks to the quick-dry formula, it will set to touch within 1–2 hours.\n* Wait 6 to 8 hours for the film to dry thoroughly. Sand the first coat very lightly with a super-fine waterproof **Emery Paper 400** to remove any trapped dust nibs, wipe it down, and apply the final **2nd Topcoat** to reveal a deep, brilliant mirror-gloss armor."
